            "old_string": "## P1: Architecture\n\n### 1. Float Tracer Redesign: DDA + Camera Plane\n**File**: `raycaster_float.c`\n\nThe float tracer uses intercept-based ray marching with separate horizontal/vertical passes. Although it computes trig at runtime (`atanf`, `sinf`, `cosf`) rather than using lookup tables, its `deltaAngle` formula duplicates the one in `tools/precalculator.c`, and its intercept-step structure mirrors the fixed-point engine's approach.\n\nRewrite as a clean DDA implementation with camera-plane FOV representation (inspired by cub3d). This is one task, not two -- DDA is the ray-marching algorithm, camera plane is the ray-generation model, and both belong together.\n\n**DDA ray march** (single loop, no trig inside):\n```c\nwhile (!hit) {\n    if (side_dist_x < side_dist_y) {\n        side_dist_x += delta_dist_x;\n        map_x += step_x;\n        side = 0;\n    } else {\n        side_dist_y += delta_dist_y;\n        map_y += step_y;\n        side = 1;\n    }\n    if (map[map_y][map_x] == WALL) hit = 1;\n}\n// Perpendicular distance eliminates fisheye without cos(deltaAngle) correction\n```\n\n**Camera plane ray generation** (no lookup tables):\n```c\ndouble camera_x = 2.0 * x / SCREEN_WIDTH - 1.0;\ndouble ray_dir_x = dir_x + plane_x * camera_x;\ndouble ray_dir_y = dir_y + plane_y * camera_x;\n// FOV = 2 * atan(plane_length) -- adjustable at runtime\n// Rotation via 2x2 matrix preserving orthogonality\n```\n\n**Why**: Makes `raycaster_float.c` a true standalone reference with zero dependency on precomputed tables. Simpler, faster, easier to verify against the fixed-point version.\n\n**Constraint**: Fixed-point tracer stays untouched (optimized for no-FPU targets).\n\n**Reference**: `externals/cub3d/src/raycasting.c`, `src/player_rotation.c`\n\n### 2. Runtime Map Configuration\n**File**: new `map_parser.c/h`\n\nDecouple map data from compiled code. Parse a text-based `.ray` format at startup:\n\n```\nT_N assets/textures/north.png\nT_S assets/textures/south.png\nT_W assets/textures/west.png\nT_E assets/textures/east.png\nF 40,40,40\nC 100,100,200\n\n1111111111\n1000000001\n100N000001\n1000000001\n1111111111\n```\n\n- Multi-pass validation: config lines, map grid, full enclosure check (flood-fill from exterior to verify every traversable cell is walled off, not just spawn-connected region)\n- Player spawn from direction character (N/S/E/W), exactly one spawn required\n- Fall back to compiled-in `raycaster_data.c` when no file argument\n- Baremetal keeps compiled-in maps; SDL gains runtime loading\n- Acceptance criteria: max map dimensions (e.g. 64x64), exactly four texture paths, RGB values 0-255, bounded file size, clear error messages on parse failure\n\n**Reference**: `externals/cub3d/src/parsing/` (5 files, ~500 LOC)\n\n### 3. Direction-Based Wall Textures (NSWE)",
